    "The latter applies particularly to Carlsmith (2022) and Cotra (2021 Cotra (, 2022)).",
    "However, the lack of academic discussion has a price: first, arguments for extreme risks from AI are often not presented as explicitly and rigorously as would be necessary to convince critical readers.",
    "This makes it hard to satisfactorily evaluate the strength of these arguments.",
    "Second, since there is no canonical and detailed exposition of the argument for existential risk from AI, it is more difficult than necessary for critics to engage with these arguments.",
    "Critics lack both a clear target to engage with and requisite motivation, since developing detailed and careful objections to blogposts and forum posts is not incentivized in academia."
